{
  "description": "The CodeBoarding project is an AI-driven code analysis and documentation generation tool designed to provide architectural insights from a codebase. It operates as a pipeline, orchestrated by a central engine that manages the flow of control and data. The process begins with fetching code from repositories, followed by deep static analysis to extract structural information. These analysis results are then fed into an AI interpretation layer, where specialized agents leverage Large Language Models (LLMs) to generate architectural insights. Finally, these insights are used by the orchestration engine to produce various output formats, including visual diagrams, while a dedicated component monitors and evaluates the system's performance.",
